condition_dsl.description:
The condition is a JSON object. The top-level key is a logical operator: "all", "any", or "not".
Inside, each clause is either an event matcher or an entity matcher.

Event matcher — checks the triggering event:
  {"event": "experiment_completed", "contradicts_includes": "$h.id"}
  {"event": "verification_failed", "linked_hypothesis_id": "$h.id"}

Entity matcher — checks the current state of an entity:
  {"entity": "hypothesis", "id": "$h.id", "state": "active"}
  {"entity": "hypothesis", "id": "$h.id", "confidence": {"lt": 0.3}}

$h is a bound variable scoped to the triggering event's primary subject
(the hypothesis that was tested or linked). Numeric comparisons: lt, lte, gt, gte, eq.

actions_dsl.description:
actions_json is a JSON array. Each element is an action object with a "type" field.
Available action types and their fields:
  {"type": "reject_hypothesis",  "reason": "string", "reason_type": "evidence|superseded|constraint"}
  {"type": "weaken_hypothesis"}
  {"type": "promote_hypothesis"}
  {"type": "create_finding",     "text": "string"}
